verses.text: And they took their journey from Elim , and all the congregation of the children of Israel came unto the wilderness of Sin , which \add is\add* between Elim and Sinai , on the fifteenth day of the second month after their departing out of the land of Egypt.
And the whole congregation of the children of Israel murmured against Moses and Aaron in the wilderness :

And the children of Israel said unto them, Would to God we had died by the hand of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in the land of Egypt , when we sat by the flesh pots , \add and\add* when we did eat bread to the full ; for ye have brought us forth into this wilderness , to kill this whole assembly with hunger. \p

¶ Then said the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* unto Moses , Behold, I will rain bread from heaven for you; and the people shall go out and gather a certain rate every day , that I may prove them, whether they will walk in my law , or no.\f + \fr 16.4 \ft a certain…: Heb. the portion of a day in his day\f*
And it shall come to pass, that on the sixth day they shall prepare \add that\add* which they bring in ; and it shall be twice as much as they gather daily.
And Moses and Aaron said unto all the children of Israel , At even , then ye shall know that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath brought you out from the land of Egypt :

And in the morning , then ye shall see the glory of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*; for that he heareth your murmurings against the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*: and what \add are\add* we , that ye murmur against us?

And Moses said , \add This shall be\add*, when the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* shall give you in the evening flesh to eat , and in the morning bread to the full ; for that the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* heareth your murmurings which ye murmur against him: and what \add are\add* we ? your murmurings \add are\add* not against us, but against the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*. \p
¶ And Moses spake unto Aaron , Say unto all the congregation of the children of Israel , Come near before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: for he hath heard your murmurings.

And it came to pass, as Aaron spake unto the whole congregation of the children of Israel , that they looked toward the wilderness , and, behold, the glory of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* appeared in the cloud. \p
¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses , saying ,

I have heard the murmurings of the children of Israel : speak unto them, saying , At even ye shall eat flesh , and in the morning ye shall be filled with bread ; and ye shall know that I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God. \p
And it came to pass, that at even the quails came up , and covered the camp : and in the morning the dew lay round about the host.
And when the dew that lay was gone up , behold, upon the face of the wilderness \add there lay\add* a small round thing , \add as\add* small as the hoar frost on the ground.

And when the children of Israel saw \add it\add*, they said one to another , It \add is\add* manna : for they wist not what it \add was\add*. And Moses said unto them, This \add is\add* the bread which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath given you to eat.\f + \fr 16.15 \ft It is…: or, What is this? or, It is a portion\f* \p

¶ This \add is\add* the thing which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath commanded , Gather of it every man according to his eating , an omer for every man , \add according to\add* the number of your persons ; take ye every man for \add them\add* which \add are\add* in his tents.\f + \fr 16.16 \ft for every…: Heb. by the poll, or, head\f*\f + \fr 16.16 \ft persons: Heb. souls\f*
And the children of Israel did so, and gathered , some more , some less.
And when they did mete \add it\add* with an omer , he that gathered much had nothing over , and he that gathered little had no lack ; they gathered every man according to his eating.
And Moses said , Let no man leave of it till the morning.
Notwithstanding they hearkened not unto Moses ; but some of them left of it until the morning , and it bred worms , and stank : and Moses was wroth with them.
And they gathered it every morning , every man according to his eating : and when the sun waxed hot , it melted. \p
¶ And it came to pass, \add that\add* on the sixth day they gathered twice as much bread , two omers for one \add man:\add* and all the rulers of the congregation came and told Moses.

And he said unto them, This \add is that\add* which the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* hath said , To morrow \add is\add* the rest of the holy sabbath unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*: bake \add that\add* which ye will bake \add to day\add*, and seethe that ye will seethe ; and that which remaineth over lay up for you to be kept until the morning.
And they laid it up till the morning , as Moses bade : and it did not stink , neither was there any worm therein.
And Moses said , Eat that to day ; for to day \add is\add* a sabbath unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: to day ye shall not find it in the field.
Six days ye shall gather it; but on the seventh day , \add which is\add* the sabbath , in it there shall be none. \p
¶ And it came to pass, \add that\add* there went out \add some\add* of the people on the seventh day for to gather , and they found none.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto Moses , How long refuse ye to keep my commandments and my laws ?

See , for that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath given you the sabbath , therefore he giveth you on the sixth day the bread of two days ; abide ye every man in his place, let no man go out of his place on the seventh day.
So the people rested on the seventh day.
And the house of Israel called the name thereof Manna : and it \add was\add* like coriander seed , white ; and the taste of it \add was\add* like wafers \add made\add* with honey. \p

¶ And Moses said , This \add is\add* the thing which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* commandeth , Fill an omer of it to be kept for your generations ; that they may see the bread wherewith I have fed you in the wilderness , when I brought you forth from the land of Egypt.
And Moses said unto Aaron , Take a pot , and put an omer full of manna therein, and lay it up before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, to be kept for your generations.
As the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* commanded Moses , so Aaron laid it up before the Testimony , to be kept.
And the children of Israel did eat manna forty years , until they came to a land inhabited ; they did eat manna , until they came unto the borders of the land of Canaan.
Now an omer \add is\add* the tenth \add part\add* of an ephah.
